    <stitle>GENERAL INSTRUMENT ELECTRONIC PROGRAMMABLE SPEEDOMETER/TACHOMETER - ASSEMBLY</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcsubsec>
        <title>ASSEMBLY</title>
        <svcproc svcproctype="IDcomponent" graphiccount="0">
            <title>Service Procedure</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">To install the odometer, position it in the housing and install the (2) screw and
                    tighten to specifications (see
                    <xref refid="x0803305"/>
                    <hotlnk document="s08033_24.xml" xrefid="x0803305">SPECIFICATIONS</hotlnk>). Connect the odometer
                    lead to the J1 pins.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">To install speedometer or tachometer gauge to the housing, position gauge to (4) pins
                    and gently push into place. The gauge case is non-conductive material so that if power were applied,
                    the case will not short out the pins.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Position housing face plate and insert the (6) screws and tighten to specifications (see
                    <xref refid="x0803305"/>
                    <hotlnk document="s08033_24.xml" xrefid="x0803305">SPECIFICATIONS</hotlnk>).
                </para>
            </step1>
        </svcproc>
    </svcsubsec>
